section.t:
The Content-ID header field included in header fields of a SIP message identifies a body part consisting of the message-body of the SIP message and:


    a MIME-Version header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Disposition header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Encoding header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-ID header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Language header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Length header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Type header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message.

A Content-ID header field included in header fields of a SIP message indicates a globally
unique identification of a body part consisting of the message-body of the SIP message and:


    a MIME-Version header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Disposition header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Encoding header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-ID header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Language header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Length header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message;

    a Content-Type header field, if included in the header fields of the SIP message.
